  "prompt": "How is WIND Mobile so cheap?",
  "response": "WIND Mobile, known as Freedom Mobile since 2016, typically offers lower prices for several reasons:\n\n1. **Competitive Market Positioning**: WIND Mobile entered the market as a challenger to established telecom companies in Canada. To attract customers, they offered competitive pricing.\n\n2. **Network Infrastructure**: Initially, WIND Mobile's network coverage was more limited compared to major providers. They invested in building and expanding their infrastructure over time, but often had lower overhead costs initially.\n\n3. **Focus on Urban Areas**: WIND Mobile focused on urban areas, where the cost of building and maintaining network infrastructure can be lower than in rural areas.\n\n4. **Simple Plans**: WIND Mobile offered straightforward plans with fewer extras, allowing them to keep prices lower.\n\n5. **MVNO Partnerships**: Freedom Mobile, previously WIND Mobile, sometimes worked as a Mobile Virtual Network Operator (MVNO) on other networks, which can be cheaper.\n\nIt\u2019s worth noting that Freedom Mobile (formerly WIND Mobile) has continued to evolve, investing in better coverage and infrastructure. Prices can vary based on the competition and market demands.",
